<div id="review_2711644614" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2711644614" />
    <a title="MG *Bury Me with My Kindle.. &amp; a REALLY Long Charger*" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger"><img alt="MG *Bury Me with My Kindle.. &amp; a REALLY Long Charger*" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595732730p2/79648381.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2711644614?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MG *Bury Me with My Kindle.. &amp; a REALLY Long Charger*" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MG *Bury Me with My Kindle.. &amp; a REALLY Long Charger*" href="/user/show/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger">MG *Bury Me with My Kindle.. &amp; a REALLY Long Charger*</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=dark">dark</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=not-a-standalone">not-a-standalone</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=beauty-and-the-beast-retelling">beauty-and-the-beast-retelling</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=freebie">freebie</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=steamy">steamy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=military">military</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=damaged-heroine">damaged-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=instalove">instalove</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=cliffhanger">cliffhanger</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79648381-mg-bury-me-with-my-kindle-a-really-long-charger?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2711644614" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7639721413435114198"><b>3 stars</b><br/><br/>This is the first book in this trilogy, and it ends on a pretty big cliffhanger. The story is about Grant, a man who has lived with dark secrets and emotional pain since he can remember. Beyond the internal demons, he also has suffered gruesome burn marks that scare many people away from him on sight; as a result, he is convinced he is an unlovable, unworthy monster. He finds a therapist (Andre) who utilizes unusual, but effective, methods and feels working with him may be his only chance</span>
  <span id="freeText7639721413435114198" style="display:none"><b>3 stars</b><br /><br />This is the first book in this trilogy, and it ends on a pretty big cliffhanger. The story is about Grant, a man who has lived with dark secrets and emotional pain since he can remember. Beyond the internal demons, he also has suffered gruesome burn marks that scare many people away from him on sight; as a result, he is convinced he is an unlovable, unworthy monster. He finds a therapist (Andre) who utilizes unusual, but effective, methods and feels working with him may be his only chance to live a somewhat normal life. As he opens up to Andre, his long held secrets begin to come to light, and Grant begins to believe that there may be a chance for him to move past these significant obstacles after all.<br /><br />Andre has other clients, one of whom he has had in his care for many years: Renata. She came to him as a terrified, orphaned, unwanted 17 year old who did not speak at all and trusted no one. Over several years, Andre was able to get her to come more and more out of her shell to where she now serves as a sex surrogate for clients with specific hang-ups related to sex. Andre believes that Grant is one of these clients, so he connects the two and things progress from there.<br /><br />What I liked:<br />--- Grant's story was interesting, and the way he revealed his secrets to Andre felt realistic for the type of person he seemed to be and the circumstances he was in<br />--- Andre is the most fascinating character in the book --- the author doesn't provide enough information about him to really understand what his background/motivations/training/etc. are yet; the mystery makes the reader want to continue on to explore this character more thoroughly<br /><br />What I didn't like:<br />--- The way Renata's story was told felt choppy and repetitive; I didn't connect with her as much as I did with Grant<br />--- There were some things that just didn't make sense <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ It isn't until almost the end of this first book that the central characters, Grant and Renata, actually meet. When they DO meet, it's supposed to be some kind of insta-love connection, though all they did was have a quick &amp; dirty bang session. It seems pretty absurd for people this damaged to toss their chips in and throw the "L" word around, then plan to move in together after knowing each other for a few hours. Especially since the day before they met, Renata had another client she had sex with that she thought she might have feelings for and even considered marrying that guy! I think it was meant by the author to be a contrast of how she felt about the other guy paling in comparison to how she felt about Grant upon meeting him, but it came across as fickle and immature. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />This is a dark read with some heavy aspects and more than unsettling discussion/descriptions of the sexual, emotional, and physical abuse of underage children by trusted adults. If that offends you or might spark a trigger, please do not read.<br /><br />Plot --- 3/5<br />Main Characters --- I feel like I need to split them out... Grant --- 4/5; Andre --- 4/5; Renata --- 2.5/5<br />Supporting Cast --- 3/5<br />Steam Level --- 3/5<br />Violence --- as mentioned above, some possible triggers in descriptions of abuse<br />Language --- Yep<br />POV --- Dual</span>
  <a data-text-id="7639721413435114198" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


