<div id="review_1139629885" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1139629885" />
    <a title="Janey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17732337-janey"><img alt="Janey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1368212259p2/17732337.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1139629885?book_show_action=true">Dec 23, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janey" href="/user/show/17732337-janey">Janey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1139629885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3166524911718869689">Brilliant!!, first 5 star read of the year!, I made a point of not reading any reviews and was really surprised, why?, there&apos;s no BDSM in it, light on the sex and I didn&apos;t realise what an integral part of the story André is!!, I was so happy I want to meet André, I want him to be real even if only for a fleeting moment, he could say &quot;pass the sugar mon cherie&quot; whilst in Starbucks and I would bask in his greatness, I love André and I&apos;m not ashamed to say it!, Anyhoo the story was really hard to r</span>
  <span id="freeText3166524911718869689" style="display:none">Brilliant!!, first 5 star read of the year!, I made a point of not reading any reviews and was really surprised, why?, there's no BDSM in it, light on the sex and I didn't realise what an integral part of the story André is!!, I was so happy I want to meet André, I want him to be real even if only for a fleeting moment, he could say "pass the sugar mon cherie" whilst in Starbucks and I would bask in his greatness, I love André and I'm not ashamed to say it!, Anyhoo the story was really hard to read in places for me but you kinda felt you were healing with both Grant and Renata and their journey together hopefully to helping and healing each other. There is a lot of evil here but you see also loads of heart and compassion, I don't know why but I loved the character Mr Brand he gave so much through his seemingly small acts of kindness to a young Renata that actually made me misty. As you read you want retribution you want answers but unfortunately I didn't realise there will be another book/s (?) but actually I don't mind at all just means more André, Grant, Renata and Mitten the hugging Kitten!! Cannot wait.</span>
