        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1301746393" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13777266475845727177"><b>3.5 - 4 TRES BIEN STARS!<br/><br/>Two tortured souls, looking for some sort of peace, Andre Chevalier will try to give them that peace.<br/><br/>Renata and Grant are strangers, both have horrific abusive pasts and are both are scarred mentally, Grant is scarred physically too. Their saviour comes in the form of Frenchman Andre.<br/><br/>I loved Andre and his quirky ways, I&apos;m dying to know his story. When I was reading, in my mind I was doing it in a French accent, more precisely Inspector Clouseau&apos;s accent. In hindsight this</b></span>
  <span id="freeText13777266475845727177" style="display:none"><b>3.5 - 4 TRES BIEN STARS!<br /><br />Two tortured souls, looking for some sort of peace, Andre Chevalier will try to give them that peace.<br /><br />Renata and Grant are strangers, both have horrific abusive pasts and are both are scarred mentally, Grant is scarred physically too. Their saviour comes in the form of Frenchman Andre.<br /><br />I loved Andre and his quirky ways, I'm dying to know his story. When I was reading, in my mind I was doing it in a French accent, more precisely Inspector Clouseau's accent. In hindsight this was probably a good thing as it kind of lightened the read in parts.<br /><br />I felt for Grant and all he went through and Renata too. I know it was a bit extreme the insta love thing they had going on but their lives and what they suffered were extreme too, so it was fitting in that retrospect. <br /><br />Would have liked to read a bit more about the H and h as a couple and not waited so long for them to get together, but that's just me!<br /><br />The ending, well it was a sort of cliffy and I will be reading book 2 when the rest of this series is out. <br />An emotional dark read that I enjoyed.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="13777266475845727177" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
