<div id="review_1334834405" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1334834405" />
    <a title="Ella  Reese" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30938224-ella-reese"><img alt="Ella  Reese" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1443719503p2/30938224.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1334834405?book_show_action=true">Jul 14, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ella  Reese" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ella  Reese" href="/user/show/30938224-ella-reese">Ella  Reese</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30938224-ella-reese?shelf=freebie">freebie</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30938224-ella-reese?shelf=dark">dark</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1334834405" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12092560232465007441">It’s difficult to say that I enjoyed this book since much of the subject matter was so dark, but I did. Abuse had an intricate but believable plot following the lives of abuse survivors and their pursuit of recovery. <br/><br/>I loved André Chevalier. He was fun, crazy, arrogant, charismatic, and a bit of a smartass. I really liked Grant as well. His secrets made him more mysterious, and I couldn’t help liking him even though he had a dark side. Most of his self-loathing was unwarranted from childhood abu</span>
  <span id="freeText12092560232465007441" style="display:none">It’s difficult to say that I enjoyed this book since much of the subject matter was so dark, but I did. Abuse had an intricate but believable plot following the lives of abuse survivors and their pursuit of recovery. <br /><br />I loved André Chevalier. He was fun, crazy, arrogant, charismatic, and a bit of a smartass. I really liked Grant as well. His secrets made him more mysterious, and I couldn’t help liking him even though he had a dark side. Most of his self-loathing was unwarranted from childhood abuse, but it was obvious that he has other secrets that have yet to be revealed. <br /><br />I was not crazy about Renata. Her childhood trauma broke my heart, but her in the present kind of annoyed me. I do like that she was so casual about her love of sex. It’s empowering that she was not ashamed of her promiscuity. However, Renata falls in love so easily it’s almost flippant. I just knew it would be instalove for her and Grant. Anyone could see that coming from a mile away. <br /><br />This one ended in a cliffy. I was thinking this was a standalone when I originally started reading it, but I’ll eventually get around to reading the next installment. I wasn’t completely enraptured by this story, but I would like to know what happens next. <br /><br />Overall, it was a respectable story of such broken people trying to overcome their demons. Three and a half stars. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12092560232465007441" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


