        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1298067999" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16207795482531865328"><b> 5 Emotional Stars </b><br/><br/><b> <u> Cliffhanger </u> </b><br/><br/><b> Abuse </b> comes in many form such as<b>:</b> physical, mental, sexual, emotional, and, verbal. <br/><br/>Grant sees himself as a monster due to his disfigurement (book 1).<br/>Grant Wilkerson is a damaged man who isolated himself due to his scars, both physical and mental. He works with a counselor, Andre Chevalier, who manages to get inside Grant&apos;s heart and brought the good person beyond his appearance.<br/><br/>Renata sees herself as a mouse due to past (book2). <br/>Renata Koreman is an amazing w</span>
  <span id="freeText16207795482531865328" style="display:none"><b> 5 Emotional Stars </b><br /><br /><b> <u> Cliffhanger </u> </b><br /><br /><b> Abuse </b> comes in many form such as<b>:</b> physical, mental, sexual, emotional, and, verbal. <br /><br />Grant sees himself as a monster due to his disfigurement (book 1).<br />Grant Wilkerson is a damaged man who isolated himself due to his scars, both physical and mental. He works with a counselor, Andre Chevalier, who manages to get inside Grant's heart and brought the good person beyond his appearance.<br /><br />Renata sees herself as a mouse due to past (book2). <br />Renata Koreman is an amazing woman with an ugly past. When she first met Andre, she was shy, mute and damaged person. Andre was able to bring out the strong woman hidden inside her.<br /><br />It’s a fantastic love story and completely different from my usual broken hero/heroine. This book have you laughing then crying the next. When Grant and Renata finally get together, their chemistry exploded but it took time to get there. Each characters have to be explain to how and why they are the way. Love it. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16207795482531865328" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
