<div id="review_1139710074" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1139710074" />
    <a title="Stacie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15992420-stacie"><img alt="Stacie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612761726p2/15992420.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1139710074?book_show_action=true">Dec 23, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacie" href="/user/show/15992420-stacie">Stacie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1139710074" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3584838190682333879">Well, this book was not at all what I expected it to be. It is a bit of a study in psychiatry and abuse counseling. Not very much romance. The subject matter is so sad and incredibly heartbreaking. Plus I&apos;m not so sure how believable Grant and Renata&apos;s connection is- it&apos;s very instant. With that being said, I&apos;ve become engrossed in Grant and Renata&apos;s story so I&apos;m moving on to Accuse. I have lots of questions and remain unconvinced that this is a good pairing. I guess we will see. I very much so </span>
  <span id="freeText3584838190682333879" style="display:none">Well, this book was not at all what I expected it to be. It is a bit of a study in psychiatry and abuse counseling. Not very much romance. The subject matter is so sad and incredibly heartbreaking. Plus I'm not so sure how believable Grant and Renata's connection is- it's very instant. With that being said, I've become engrossed in Grant and Renata's story so I'm moving on to Accuse. I have lots of questions and remain unconvinced that this is a good pairing. I guess we will see. I very much so want them both to be happy. Be warned, this one ends quite abruptly with a cliffhanger. Happy reading.<br /><br />PS As always, I absolutely loved Andre' Cavalier!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3584838190682333879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


